entries.meaning: A pointed stick used to make a fence.
examples: The boys continued hitting the tennis ball with pailings snatched from a fence  […]

Gentlemen must have observed that many of the nurserymen’s plantations were wide and extensive, some of them covering several acres; and that their palings and fences were for the most part low, and might be so weak and out of repair, as to afford a very insufficient security against the inroads of robbers and spoilers.

entries.meaning: (Caribbean) A fence made of galvanized sheeting.
examples: He worked badly. He had to paint a large sign on a corrugated iron paling. Doing letters on a corrugated surface was bad enough; to paint a cow and a gate, as he had to, was maddening.
